backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3613196\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 13, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gbk1665702628600.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gbk1665702628600.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gbk1665702628600.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gbk1665702628600\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Tool Tip Text (ToolTipText)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">This property specifies the text to be displayed when the cursor is positioned over the widget. It can be a string up to 1024 bytes.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__p_d108302e1_d108303e1_d108304e1\">ToolTipText<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code><code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">TextString</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code></p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__section_ipg_qjf_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d140295e62\">Description</h2>\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__p_d108308e1_d108309e1_d108310e1\">The tooltip is displayed when the cursor hovers over\n        the field. Tooltips can be displayed in non-modal forms, and in modal forms that have focus.\n        No tool tip is shown on disabled forms (such as a modal form that has opened another form).\n        They can only be displayed when Uniface is active.<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__note_nr3_rjf_1xb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Uniface takes the current MS Windows desktop settings for Tool Tips. To display Unicode\n          characters, this property must be set to a Unicode font, for example Arial Unicode\n          MS.</div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__section_cw4_sjf_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d140295e73\">Setting in ProcScript</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__p_d108314e1_d108315e1_d108316e1\">You can set the value of the property in ProcScript\n        using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$properties</span> or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldproperties</span>\n        functions.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__p_d108317e1_d108318e1_d108319e1\">If you set the ToolTipText property with\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$properties</span>, every occurrence of the field shows the same tool tip. If\n        you set it with <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldproperties</span>, the tool tip is only shown on the\n        current occurrence.</p>\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__p_d108320e1_d108321e1_d108322e1\">To ensure that the desired occurrence is the current\n        one, use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">setocc</span> prior to <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldproperties</span>, for example\n        during initialization (when retrieving data) or when the user performs an action (such as\n        clicking a button). <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">setocc</span> does not switch the focus, so no triggers are\n        fired, which could interfere with displaying tool tips.<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__note_brw_vjf_1xb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> It is not possible to change tool tip text if the ProcScript engine\n          has no implicit focus, for example, if the focus is set to a painted field and the user\n          just moves the mouse over different fields without clicking nor pressing any\n        thing.</div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__section_v53_xjf_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d140295e111\">Applies to</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__ul_spn_yjf_1xb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__li_d42305e1_d42306e1_d42307e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fxi1688449052174.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fxi1688449052174.html\" title=\"The ucheckbox widget enables the user to set a Boolean value in a form component. Uniface provides a logical widget called CheckBox, which is mapped to ucheckbox.\">ucheckbox (CheckBox)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__li_d42308e1_d42309e1_d42310e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kzn1665703126224.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kzn1665703126224.html\" title=\"The ucolorbox widget displays a color value, either a color name or RGB value, in a color box in a form component. Uniface provides a logical widget called ColorBox, which is mapped to ucolorbox.\">ucolorbox (ColorBox)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__li_d42311e1_d42312e1_d42313e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jrc1665702631553.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jrc1665702631553.html\" title=\"The CommandButton is a logical widget that enables a user to initiate an action by clicking the button.\">CommandButton</a>—takes precedence over a tool tip defined using the\n            <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Tool Tip</span> property </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__li_d42314e1_d42315e1_d42316e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fud1688450548955.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fud1688450548955.html\" title=\"The udropdownlist widget is a field-level widget that can display a list of valid options in a list below the input field, so that the user can select one. It is applicable only to form components.\">udropdownlist (DropDownList)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__li_d42317e1_d42318e1_d42319e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"klb1688454363706.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/klb1688454363706.html\" title=\"Default logical widget for entering and displaying data in a field in a Form or Report.\">EditBox</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__li_d42320e1_d42321e1_d42322e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lxc1665703126500.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lxc1665703126500.html\" title=\"The upicture widget is used to displays the contents of an Image field. Uniface provides a logical widget called Picture, which is mapped to upicture.\">upicture (Picture)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gbk1665702628600__li_d42323e1_d42324e1_d42325e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lxs1665702651483.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lxs1665702651483.html\" title=\"The uspinbutton widget enables the user to enter or select a numeric value by clicking a button to increase or decrease a value by a predefined interval within a predefined range. Uniface provides a logical widget called SpinButton, which is mapped to uspinbutton.\">uspinbutton (SpinButton)</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613196\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613196\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Tool Tip Text (ToolTipText) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 13, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Tool Tip Text (ToolTipText) This property specifies the text to be displayed when the cursor is positioned over the widget. It can be a string up to 1024 bytes. ToolTipText = \" TextString \" Description The tooltip is displayed when the cursor hovers over the field. Tooltips can be displayed in non-modal forms, and in modal forms that have focus. No tool tip is shown on disabled forms (such as a modal form that has opened another form). They can only be displayed when Uniface is active. Note: Uniface takes the current MS Windows desktop settings for Tool Tips. To display Unicode characters, this property must be set to a Unicode font, for example Arial Unicode MS. Setting in ProcScript You can set the value of the property in ProcScript using the $properties or $fieldproperties functions. If you set the ToolTipText property with $properties , every occurrence of the field shows the same tool tip. If you set it with $fieldproperties , the tool tip is only shown on the current occurrence. To ensure that the desired occurrence is the current one, use setocc prior to $fieldproperties , for example during initialization (when retrieving data) or when the user performs an action (such as clicking a button). setocc does not switch the focus, so no triggers are fired, which could interfere with displaying tool tips. Note: It is not possible to change tool tip text if the ProcScript engine has no implicit focus, for example, if the focus is set to a painted field and the user just moves the mouse over different fields without clicking nor pressing any thing. Applies to ucheckbox (CheckBox) ucolorbox (ColorBox) CommandButton —takes precedence over a tool tip defined using the Tool Tip property udropdownlist (DropDownList) EditBox upicture (Picture) uspinbutton (SpinButton) Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}